com.doetsch.tuple

Class TuplePair<A,B>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.doetsch.tuple.TuplePair<A,B>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - The data-type of the first element in the tuple.
    B - The data-type of the second element in the tuple.

    public class TuplePair<A,B>
extends Object
    TuplePair is the realization of a two-element tuple. It is intended to extend the functionality of Java by implementing tuples. TuplePair is immutable.
    Author:
    Jacob Wesley Doetsch
